					<h2>Purpose of Revenue Trends</h2>
					<p>Forecasting is difficult. Less than 50% of deals actually close as forecast. Understanding the recent past helps you to assess the risks in your current forecast.</p>
					<p>Revenue Trends helps you to understand the accuracy of your sales forecasting process by showing what happened to the deals that existed 30, 60 or 90 days ago, organized by Forecast category, Revenue Type, team or individual sales person.</p>
	   
		
		
					<div class="more_info">
					
						<p>You can look back at the opportunities in each Forecast category to see whether the opportunities progressed as expected over the reporting period.</p>
						
						<p>By looking at Projected deals that are still open, were lost, or have changed materially in value, you may be able to spot potentially similar outcomes in your current forecast. This informs the accuracy of your current forecast and helps you to uncover weaknesses in process, qualification, and deal progressions. </p>
		
					</div>
					<p>
