					<h2>How to Use Revenue Trends with your Team</h2>
					<p>There are three areas in the Revenue Trends screen:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Revenue Outlook Trends</li>
						<li>What Happened to the Revenue Outlook</li>
						<li>Detailed Changes to the Revenue Outlook</li>
					</ul>
					<p>These areas of analysis are explored below:</p>
					<div class="more_info">					
					<h2>Revenue Outlook Trends</h2>
					<p>The Revenue Outlook Trends chart summarizes:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>the Forecast status of the opportunities that existed 30, 60, or 90 days ago</li>
						<li>their current status </li>
					</ul>
					<p>Only opportunities that existed on the past date are included in the analysis. Opportunities that entered the system since that date are not represented.  This maintains the integrity of the ‘what happened’ analysis.</p>
					<h2>What Happened to the Revenue Outlook</h2>
					<p>This chart shows the current state of the historical opportunities for each Forecast category. </p>
					<p>Forecast categories are listed vertically, and the horizontal stacked bars show today's distribution of the opportunities that belonged in each Forecast category at the start of the reporting period.</p>
					<p>Ideally, a good percentage of Projected opportunities will have moved to Won, some of the Possible opportunities will have progressed to Projected or Won, and some of the Unlikely opportunities will also have progressed. </p>
					<p> You may also see regressions, where opportunities that were Projected are now Possible, Unlikely, or Lost.</p>
					<p>Moving from 90 Days Ago to 30 Days Ago, you should see fewer changes, and ideally no losses arising from Projected opportunities. Such a regression usually indicates a late-stage loss.</p>
					<h2>Detailed Changes to the Revenue Outlook</h2>
					<p>Beneath the two charts on the Revenue Trends screen you'll see a detailed table of how opportunities have moved from their Forecast category at the start of the period (90, 60, or 30 days ago) to today.</p>
					<p>The leftmost column shows the the value and number of opportunities in that Forecast category at the beginning of the period. </p>
					<p>Moving rightwards you see where those opportunities are today, and any change in the value of the opportunities since the start of the period.</p>
					<p>Opportunities with a green background have progressed from:</p>
					<ul>
						<li>Unlikely to Possible, Projected or Won</li>
						<li>Possible to Projected or Won</li>
						<li>Projected to Won</li>
					</ul>
					<p>Opportunities with an orange background have regressed.</p>
					<p>Click any number to see the opportunities that make up that number, along with any changes in Stage, Value, Close Date and Close Probability for each.</p>
		
					</div>
					<p><a href="javascript:void[0]" class="more_info_link">More...</a></p>
