				<div class="point_text">
					<h2>Best Practice</h2>
					<ul>
						<li>Review Revenue Outlook Trends monthly with each team member</li>
						<p>The purpose of these calls is to learn from a comparison of expected outcome and actual outcome for Projected and other opportunities. </p>
						<p>This process enables the manager and seller to align on any remediation needed so that they can:</p>
						<ul>
							<li>more accurately set expectations, so that neither party is surprised by the outcome</li>
							<li>identify where there may be risks to the accuracy of the forecast</li>
						</ul>
					</ul>
		
					<div class="more_info">
						<ul>
							<li>Ask the Salesperson to prepare in advance</li>
							<p>To have a productive call, both manager and seller should have the requisite information already to hand. </p>
							<p>These calls should focus on improving behavior to attain more accurate future projections, saving time for both seller and manager.</p>
							<p>Where there are deviations between expected outcomes and actual outcomes, ask: </p>
							<ul>
								<li>What is the root cause of the inaccuracy, on a deal-by-deal basis? </li>
								<li>What should have been done differently? </li>
								<li>What changes should be made in the next month to refine the outlook?</li>
							</ul>
						</ul>
						<ul>
							<li>Use Insights to examine four key areas:</li>
							<ul>
								<li>Projected Analysis: What has been the movement in Projected opportunities?</li>
								<li>Movement: What opportunities have moved forwards or backwards through the Forecast categories?</li>
								<li>Value Change: Are Projected opportunities increasing or decreasing in value as they progress?</li>
								<li>Won / Lost Deals Analysis: Which Forecast categories did Won / Lost deals come from?</li>
							</ul>
						</ul>
					</div>
					
